/* Attribute's meaning
 * -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 * kcl --------> kony layout type (hflex / vflex / fflex)
 * kfb --------> This is value of kr attribute, which means kony-fake-border
 * ko ---------> kony orientation for widgets like, CheckBoxGroup/RadioButtonGroup/Slider etc.
 * kr ---------> kony role name for our internal plugins/sub role
 * kt ---------> kony theme, for widgets like Calendar/Switch etc.
 * kv ---------> kony widget view type, for widgets like SegmentedUI2 etc.
 * kw ---------> kony widget name
 * kwf --------> kony widget fragment, like calendar popup can render in any context
 * kwg --------> kony widget gesture, can be found in Slider/Images2 etc.
 * kwh --------> kony widget handler
 * kwi --------> kony widget index (e.g. widget inside segment)
 * kwo --------> kony widget owner (widgets inside segment template will have this)
 * kwp --------> kony widget path for automation purpose (e.g. formId_segmentId[0,0]_templateId_buttonId)
 * -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 */
